	line `Keeping his toes still. No blame. Continued perseverance furthers.`
	line `Keeping his calves still. He cannot rescue him whom he follows. His heart is not glad.`
	line `Keeping his hips still. Making his sacrum stiff. Dangerous. The heart suffocates.`
	line `Keeping his trunk still. No blame.`
	line `Keeping his jaws still. The words have order. Remorse disappears.`
	line `Noblehearted keeping still. Good fortune.`
